# Exit Status


every command we run on shell gives some status .
It is called as exit status of a particular command given .

very exit command gives a value that ranges between 0-255

# these numbers are categorized into 2 types
$ success & $ failure

here the value (0) denotes success

and the rest (1-255) denotes failure.

*************************************

In the shell scripting to Refer the Exit Status of the latest command Executed
we can refer a variable ?.

to see the status we can use

echo $?

it will show the status as soon as the command is executed .

